Preconditions:
The input array "heights" must not be null.
The input array "heights" must have at least one element.
The input array "heights" must only contain non-negative integers.
The input integer "bricks" must be non-negative.
The input integer "ladders" must be non-negative.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer representing the furthest building index that can be reached.
The returned index is within the range of the input array "heights".
The method does not modify the input array "heights".
The method does not modify the input integers "bricks" and "ladders".
The method uses the given ladders and bricks optimally to reach the furthest building index.